The Nigerian Railway Corporation generated N5.70billion revenue from passengers in 2021, the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) says. This is contained in the NBS Rail Transportation Data for last year released in Abuja yesterday. The report show that the total revenue generated from passengers in 2020 was N1.75 billion. The 2021 revenue, the NBS said, represents a 226.44 per cent increase.   CBN: Payment of overseas tuition fees won’t rise next…     Global manufacturing increased by 4.2% in Q1     Senate probes Shell over JV breach   The report shows that the total revenue generated in 2020, amounting to a 226.44 per cent increase. The bureau said over 2.7 million passengers travelled by train last year compared to one million recorded in 2020, representing a 166.03 per cent increase. Similarly, the report showed a total of 168,301 tonnes of goods were transported last year as against 87,440 recorded in 2020, showing a growth rate of 92.48 per cent. In addition, the report showed the revenue generated from goods last year amounted to N317.57 million, higher by 12.87 per cent compared to N281.35 million in 2020. “Other income receipts in 2021 stood at N66.80 million, higher than the N5.19 million recorded in the preceding year.”